        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 20 at 6:15PM CDT by NWS Huntsville AL</headline>
        <description>At 615 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Cherokee, or 12 miles west of Tuscumbia, moving south at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Red Bay, Cherokee, Malone, Pogo, Mt Hester, Cedar Creek Reservoir,
Srygley Church, Allsboro, Maud, and Barton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
